[normal]Written evidence from Her [bold]Majesty’s [bold]Inspectorate of [bold]Constabulary [CST0015][bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Her Majesty's Inspectorate of Constabulary (HMIC) welcomes the opportunity to contribute to the 
[normal]Public Administration
[normal] Select Committee inquiry 
[normal]into 
[normal]crime statistics.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]HMIC is an independent body which inspects 
[normal]and reports on 
[normal]the efficiency and effectiveness of policing in England and Wales on behalf of the public. We conduct inspections on a range of issues 
[normal]–
[normal] both on our
[normal] own, and 
[normal]jointly 
[normal]with other inspectorates in the criminal justice system. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Our written submission of evidence 
[normal]respond
[normal]s
[normal] to the committee
[normal]’
[normal]s questions by 
[normal]provid
