[normal] The National Crime Recording Standard
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](NCRS) is a standard for recording crime in accordance with the
[normal] law.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]It is based on applying legal definitions of crime to victim’s reports. The aim of NCRS is to
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]be victim focussed and maintain a consistent data set of recorded
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]crime allegations across all forces. See 
[normal]https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-national-crime-recording-standard-ncrs-what-you-need-to-know
[normal] 
